content.description: Stand start with a right hand crimp and a left hand crimp/mini-pinch. From there, reach a left hand sloper, follow with the right to another sloper, raise the feet, gain the right hand sidepull, and work the remaining bumps on top to finish it off.
content.protection: A pad should do it, the landing is very good.
content.location: It climbs the southern section of Originator's east face.

content.description: Sit start with a pair of jugs and a heel hook. From there, crank up to a left hand sloping edge, match, move up to a good bump, reach a pair of incut edges, and then get a right hand pinch and the eventual jugs on top.
content.protection: The immediate landing good, but there are several rocks surrounding it. A pair of pads would be good.
content.location: It climbs the northwest face of Originator.

content.description: Stand start with right and left hand crimps about six feet off the deck. From there, gain the high foot edges, make a big reach to a left hand edge, follow with the right hand to the lip, and achieve the eventual send using the good bumps on top.
content.protection: A pair of pads should work, the landing has a few rocks in the fall zone but is overall good.
content.location: It climbs the center east face of Originator.
